<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 6:45PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central Gray
and northern Donley Counties through 715 PM CDT...
At 645 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Lake Mcclellan, or 15 miles north of Clarendon,
moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Howardwick, Alanreed, Lake Mcclellan and Greenbelt Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
